 &QL; 
 &UR; DATA:  &LR; New materials described in a scientific journal this week
could help boost the data-storage capacity of PC hard disks as much
as seventy-ivefold in three to five years, making it possible to
store whole libraries of digital movies and music on a single
drive.  &UR; BY HENRY NORR &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; ROBERTSON:  &LR; The investment bank Robertson Stephens has taken
hundreds of companies public during the past few years. Now, the
San Francisco firm may come to market with its own initial public
offering. Fleet Boston Financial Corp., the giant New England bank
that owns Robertson Stephens, is weighing a spin-off of a minority
stake in the firm to the public, sources familiar with the matter
said.  &UR; BY SAM ZUCKERMAN &QL;  &LR; 
