<P>
   RAMPAGE-ITHACA (Ithaca, N.Y.) _ In rampage killing cases around
the country, people who knew the killers often said they alerted
police about strange behavior beforehand, but were told by police
that their hands were tied. Ithaca, in a system that policing
experts say is unmatched in the country, has tried to deal with
this problem. When police here receive a report that someone is
behaving bizarrely, making threats or talking suicide, a police
officer and a mental health clinic supervisor are sent together to
assess the situation. By Laurie Goodstein. '
