   CARMEL-PROGRESS (Carmel by the Sea, Calif.) _ The days of having
to go to the post office to pick up mail are ending for the
residents of Carmel, Calif. Home delivery is coming _ and with it,
something this quirky town has never seen before: street numbers.
Now, residents will no longer have to tell FedEx or UPS, or more
importantly, 911, that they live on Hollyhock, 3 doors down from
Sparrow Road, or at Stone Owl Cottage. But in a town which has kept
out street lights, fast food and neon, not everyone thinks this is
progress.
