<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0905 -- The best food in Sydney doesn't start in the
chic bistros that have multiplied during the lead-up to the
Olympics. It begins where it has for decades: the Sydney Fish
Market. It's here when Asian influences combine with trafitional
fare to create Australia's hip ``Mod-Oz'' cuisine. (Auchmutey,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 4-column color
illustration of an Australian chef preparing meals.
