<P>
   FOOD-CONVERSATION _ In Italy, pasta is not about ``a bunch of
sauce over something starchy,'' explains Susan Hermann Loomis,
author of the Italian Farmhouse Cookbook, as she prepared pasta for
a crowd recently at Cook's Warehouse. I learned had done just about
every wrong when it comes to cooking pasta. A pot too small. No
salt in the water. Overcooking. We walk through the steps for
perfect pasta preparation. (Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
