<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ A gardening column by Lee May. This week:
Readers offer opinions about a strange insect Lee spotted on his
porch and they have seen in their gardens. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PLASTIC _ Remember when mere mention of the word plastic evoked
images of cheap stuff? A formal dinner served with _ gasp _ plastic
knives and forks. An English garden strewn with plastic lawn
chairs. A weathered tombstone adorned with plastic roses. Not
anymore. These days, plastics are commanding a level of respect _
and often high prices _ that's earning them a spot in even homes on
the right side of the track. ``Better plastics are available today,
and people are finally realizing you can mix them with pieces from
the entire 20th century,'' said Scott Reilly of retromodern.com, at
Atlanta retailer that specializes in plastic furnishings and
accessories.(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-NOTES _ The New York Times is tinkering with its best
seller list again, adding three more categories to the children's
list -- picture books, chapter books and paperbacks -- and running
them on a rotating basis. That means we'll be seeing less of Harry
Potter on the list . . . Melissa Etheridge has signed a deal to
write a memoir about motherhood and music . . . . Anthony Hopkins
will star in movie version of Stephen King's ``Hearts in
Atlantis.'' (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 17.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-PSYCHO _ Video pick: ``American Psycho.'' (StMurray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-RINGEL _ With ``Nurse Betty'' opening on Friday, Eleanor
Ringel Gillespie looks at movies involving nurses, including
``MASH.'' (Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 19.
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-GOSPEL _ Sonia Murray reviews BeBe Winans gospel CD ``Love
And Freedom.'' B-. (SoMurray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-MINIS _ Mini reviews of new albums. Options include jazz
of Michael White, Latin pop of Gisselle, country of Hot Club of
Cowtown. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
