   HOSPITAL-SURVEY (Boston) _ Bay State hospitals will keep secret
results of their second big patient satisfaction survey. And the
Picker Institute, which conducted the survey, is in trouble over
the decision. By Larry Tye. 1360 words.
</P>
<P>
   DOCTORS-ROLE (Undated) _ The world of medicine has been turned
upside down, raising doubts about whether doctors are trained
properly, whether patients know who to go to for what, and whether
insurers and money are driving the system rather than what patients
need and doctors know how to do. By Larry Tye. 1660 words.
</P>
