end-of-session negotiations between congressional leaders and
President Clinton, House Republicans led by Conference Chairman
J.C. Watts, R-Okla., declined to support an end-of-session
compromise offered by Speaker Dennis Hastert to pair a minimum wage
increase sought by Clinton with tax cuts sought by Republicans.
(Mollison, Cox News Service). 14.
