   WWII-MEMORIAL _ WASHINGTON _ Opponents of the proposed World War
II Memorial gained an influential ally Wednesday when the Advisory
Council on Historic Preservation, an independent federal agency
that advises the president and Congress, called the memorial's
design inappropriate for its proposed place on the national Mall.
(Dart).
