<P>
   WRESTLING-KILLER _ For the Extreme Championship Wrestling TV
Title Match in March, Rob Van Dam, leg in a cast, rode on the
shoulders of another wrestler out of the smoke-filled tunnel and
past cheering fans pressed up against the metal barricades. For the
occasion, which included slamming a wrestler named Rhino into a
table, Van Dam wore the Arena Football jersey of his late friend,
Bobby Duncum Jr.
</P>
<P>
   Just a couple of months prior to the March show, Van Dam was in
Allentown, Pa., signing autographs at a memorial show for another
late wrestling buddy, Gary Albright. Van Dam has lost three close
friends in the wrestling business, Louis ``Spicolli'' Mucciolo Jr.
two years ago and Albright and Duncum since January. Albright, at
36, was the oldest. Duncum was 34 and Mucciolo, 27. ``With Louie, I
hadn't been there before,'' Van Dam said. ``The more it happens,
the less shocked I am.'' (Maher, Austin American-Statesman) WITH
PHOTOS
</P>
