   SCIENCE (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-INDIANS-CANNIBALISM (Undated) - Researchers have found the
first direct evidence of cannibalism among prehistoric Indians in
the Southwest, belying the image of these people as peaceful
farmers. Among chopped up bones, they found human feces containing
digested muscle fiber. By John Noble Wilford. (1000 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SPACE-SHUTTLE (Washington) - Space shuttle Atlantis is safe
and ready to lift off Friday on a visit to the International Space
Station, which is now the size of a 14-story building in space. By
Warren E. Leary. (800 words)
</P>
