   LASCALA-OPERA-STANDEES (Rome) - When the season starts next week at
Milan's La Scala opera house, the 200 standing-room places of the first and
second galleries will no longer be on sale. This is tragic news for its
habitual dwellers, the feared and respected ``loggionisti,'' the
ardent  opera buffs who sit or stand in the  galleries  and   are said to
dictate the failure or success of a performer, a conductor or even an opera
at the theater. By Elisabetta Povoledo.
