   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-ROUNDUP (Undated) _ Al Gore lays out a 191-page
blueprint for ``a new prosperity'' in America, with 10 million new
high-tech jobs, expanded home ownership and a one-third boost in
family income over 10 years. George W. Bush charges that Gore has
promised ``more than he can possibly deliver'' and is setting the
stage for a resumption of federal ``red ink'' spending. By STEWART
M. POWELL.
</P>
