</P>
<P>
   TIRE-DEATHS (Washington) _ Bridgestone/Firestone Inc. officials,
in a remarkable admission, apologize for the defective tires that
have been blamed for 88 deaths. By JENNIFER HOYT.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-FBI (Washington) _ Senate leaders and privacy advocates
warn that a new FBI program to police the Internet threatens to
slow the growth of e-commerce and the high-tech industry. The
e-mail-sniffing system, known as Carnivore, allows agents to sift
messages to and from a targeted suspect out of the full stream of
data passing through an Internet service provider, like America
Online. By MARK HELM.
</P>
