</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-SURPLUS (Austin, Texas) _ Texas Comptroller Carole Keeton
Rylander says the state ended its fiscal year with $45 million more
in the bank than expected, pushing the budget surplus to $1.45
billion. By KATHY WALT.
</P>
<P>
   STORM-SURVIVORS (Galveston, Texas) _ A 104-year-old survivor of
the 1900 Galveston hurricane says she still remembers the storm
that killed thousands of people in the Gulf Coast city. By KEVIN
MORAN and SHANNON TOMPKINS.
</P>
<P>
   NASA-SHUTTLE (Cape Canaveral, Fla.) _ Ground teams hustle to
catch up with preparations to launch the shuttle Atlantis to the
international space station on Friday. A lightning strike delayed
some of the preparations. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HELEN-THOMAS (Washington) _ When presidential candidates find
their issues aren't selling with the electorate, they usually warn
that the other party's policies would weaken national security.
That's what Republicans George W. Bush and Dick Cheney are doing
now _ raising a red flag that both Republicans and Democrats have
used successfully in the past. By HELEN THOMAS.
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
