<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ While Al Gore and George W. Bush
zoom from state to state searching for votes, Bill Clinton blithely
circumnavigates the globe doing his own thing in his own way. With
less than five months left in his presidency, Clinton has
intensified his efforts to leave his mark on world and national
affairs. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON.
</P>
