 &HT;    
 &HT;    BERNARD GLADSTONE'S ``HOME IMPROVEMENT QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS''
for Sun., Sep. 24, 2000, which included:
 &HT;    _Nasty odor coming from sink drain? Making sure trap is filled
with water usually solves the problem (comes with illustration).
 &HT;    _How to fix a toilet that ``runs by itself.''
 &HT;    _How to get those stubborn applique marks off the bottom of the
tub.
