<P>
   CITIGROUP-ASSOCIATES (New York) - Continuing its campaign to
become the dominant financial services provider around the globe,
Citigroup said Wednesday that it would buy the Associates First
Capital Corp., the biggest American consumer-finance company, for
about $31.1 billion in stock. The acquisition, Citigroup's largest
since its controversial formation in 1998, would give Citigroup a
significant position in consumer lending in Japan and a few other
countries. It also would improve Citigroup's standing in the credit
card and commercial leasing businesses. By Patrick McGeehan.
