   SEAGRAMS-MP3-MUSIC (New York) - In a victory for old line music
companies over an online music start-up, a federal judge ruled on
Wednesday that MP3.com willfully violated copyrights and awarded
Universal Music Group $25,000 per CD, a penalty that could reach as
much as $250 million. Judge Jed S. Rakoff of U.S. District Court in
Manhattan said some Internet companies ``may have a misconception
that, because their technology is somewhat novel, they are somehow
immune from the ordinary applications of laws of the United States,
including copyright law.'' By Amy Harmon.
