<P>
   PLASTIC _ Remember when mere mention of the word plastic evoked
images of cheap stuff? A formal dinner served with _ gasp _ plastic
knives and forks. An English garden strewn with plastic lawn
chairs. A weathered tombstone adorned with plastic roses. Not
anymore. These days, plastics are commanding a level of respect _
and often high prices _ that's earning them a spot in even homes on
the right side of the track. ``Better plastics are available today,
and people are finally realizing you can mix them with pieces from
the entire 20th century,'' said Scott Reilly of retromodern.com, at
Atlanta retailer that specializes in plastic furnishings and
accessories.(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
