<P>
   FBO-MILEHIGH _ Falcons quarterback Chris Chandler has described
Denver's Mile High Stadium as the ``toughest place to play in the
NFL.'' Coach Dan Reeves has called it the ``greatest outdoor
stadium'' in the league. What makes Mile High so unique? Most of it
centers around the 80,000 fans that pack the facility each game and
the noise that they generate, making it difficult for opposing
players to hear themselves on the field. The Falcons have attempted
to simulate the noise level during practice this week, but Chandler
admits it's nearly impossible to match the noise level at Mile
High. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
