<SLUG> BC-AUDIO-GOSPEL07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Gospel truth? Winans needs helping hand
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   It almost seems blasphemous to say anything less than laudatory
about one of contemporary gospel's best and most resonant voices.
But BeBe Winans gets by here with a whole lot of help from his
friends. (The exception being the uninspired team-up with
sophisticated crooners Joe and Brian McKnight on ``Coming Back
Home.'') Luckily, Stevie Wonder steps in two tracks later playing
the Hammond organ, harmonica and a selection from an album he
recorded at the height of his R&AMP;B career _ the 1973 single ``Jesus
Children of America.'' Then on ``Everyday,'' '80s singer Stephanie
Mills is as compelling as she ever was in ``The Wiz.''
</P>
<P>
   'Love &AMP; Freedom'
</P>
<P>
   BeBe / Motown / 13 tracks / Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _Sonia Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  O N T H E W E B : More on BeBe Winans and Motown Records:
www.bebewinans.com and www.motown.com.
</P>
