   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-SAFETY (Undated) _ To prevent school violence, teachers
and principals should be on the lookout for students who are
fascinated by bloodshed, unusually heartbroken over a failed
relationship or who look up to destructive figures such as Satan or
Hitler, FBI says. By Scott Greenberger. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   ALLERGY-SEASON (Undated) _ We hear to hear it every year: This
fall and spring will be one of the worst for allergy sufferers. But
this year will really, really be one of the worst, thanks to the
damp, cool summer that ruined many vacations but fostered
tall-growing ragweed plants. By Richard Saltus. 900 words.
</P>
