ruling in federal court when a judge says MP3.com must pay $25,000
per CD that it made available via the Internet. The judge said the
penalty, which could reach $250 million, was a warning to other
Internet companies about violating copyright laws. By Stephanie
Stoughton. 1000 words.
</P>
