   SEAGRAMS-MP3-MUSIC (New York) _ In a victory for old line music
companies over an online music start-up, a federal judge rules that
MP3.com willfully violated copyrights and awards Universal Music
Group $25,000 per CD, a penalty that could reach as much as $250
million. By Amy Harmon. (Scheduled to move by 8:45 p.m. ET in ``f''
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   WTIMOR-U.N.-KILLINGS (United Nations) _ An armed mob stormed
into a U.N. refugee office in West Timor, demolishing the office
and beating to death three unarmed U.N. workers, including an
American, and touching off repercussions of outrage at the
Millennium Summit meeting of world leaders here. By Christopher S.
Wren. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
