<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A2-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SEVERAL GUESSES ABOUT 7UP
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ What does the 7 in 7UP stand for? _ L.A., Chicago
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ There are several theories about why drink inventor
Charles Grigg chose the name 7UP, but the most likely is that it
was inspired by a cattle brand, according to Jeffrey L. Rodengen,
author of the book ``The Legend of Dr Pepper/Seven-Up.''
</P>
<P>
   Other possibilities: He named it after a winning roll in a dice
game, after the drink's 7-ounce bottles or after a belief that
``his new drink would cure mankind's seven hangovers,'' Rodengen
said. ``Grigg never explained exactly why he came up with the
name.''
</P>
<P>
   When the drink debuted in 1929 a few weeks before the stock
market crash, it was called Bib-Label Lithiated Lemon-Lime Soda. It
was quickly renamed.
</P>
<P>
   To order Rodengen's book for $39.95 plus shipping, call (800)
900-2665 or visit the Web site www.writestuffbooks.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ What year was the children's show ``Shenanigans'' on
TV, and who appeared on it? _ C.S., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ ``Shenanigans,'' a game show in which two children
competed on a life-size Milton Bradley game board, aired from 1964
to 1965.
</P>
<P>
   Broadway performer Stubby Kaye hosted the show and announcer
Kenny Williams appeared as Kenny the Cop. Many stunts that children
performed to win prizes were based on Milton Bradley games such as
Time Bomb and Operation.
</P>
<P>
   ``Money was given out as Shenanaganzas, which were redeemable
later as trading stamps like you got at the grocery store,'' the
Web site TV Party.Com states. ``The commercials are all for Milton
Bradley products as well, which proves that Saturday morning toy
tie-ins go back a long way.''
</P>
<P>
   TV Party publishes a short video clip from ``Shenanigans'' on
its Web site at tvparty.com/lostshenanigans.html.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Where can I write to Ray Romano? _ U.C., via the
Internet
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Write to him in care of William Morris Agency, 151 El
Camino Drive, Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   The 42-year-old actor and comedian is up for three Emmy Awards
this year, including a nomination for Lead Actor in a Comedy
Series. The ceremony will air at 7 p.m. Sunday on ABC.
</P>
<P>
   Romano is writing a film with longtime friend Kevin James, a
fellow stand-up comedian from New York. James appeared on
``Everybody Loves Raymond'' before starring in ``King of Queens.'' &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL;   &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
