<P>
   (NYT50) NEW YORK -- Sept. 6, 2000 -- TEN-USOPEN-8 -- Serena
Williams fractured her racket on the court as her game fell apart,
and Lindsay Davenport emerged from the shadows as a forgotten
former champion to a berth in the U.S. Open semifinals. Williams,
the defending champion who was so eager to meet her sister, Venus,
in the final, succumbed to her own impatience and Davenport's deep,
sizzling groundstrokes in a 6-4, 6-2 rout Wednesday night. A
dejected Williams during her loss to Davenport. (G. Paul
Burnett/The New York Times)
