For many American cities, technology is causing visual blight. Cell
phone towers, satellite dishes, telephone poles, and other
communication equipment is altering the landscape. The Southern New
England Telephone building in downtown New London, an its
communications aerials, towers over the local scenery. (George
Ruhe/The New York Times)
