<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-AIKMAN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS OWNER TELLS AIKMAN TO SIT OUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ A consenting Troy Aikman will follow owner Jerry
Jones' directive not to suit up Sunday night for the Cowboys' game
at Arizona, because of the medical risks associated with multiple
concussions.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman suffered his eighth-known concussion over a 12-year NFL
career in the season opener Sunday against Philadelphia. It was his
third concussion in his past 10 games.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not easy \Rto accept\S ... but logically, it's probably
the right decision, the smart decision,'' said Aikman, who was
sacked four times and knocked down four more times in a total of 15
plays against the blitz-happy Eagles.
</P>
<P>
   Now, Aikman learns that his next concussion, according to
medical opinion, could sideline him ``four to six weeks, minimum.''
</P>
<P>
   Explaining his frustration and the nature of concussions, Aikman
added, ``It's just difficult not to go out and play when you feel
like you can play.''
</P>
<P>
   Retirement is not a consideration, Aikman said, ``\Rbecause\S I
don't feel the risks outweigh the enjoyment that I still get from
playing right now.''
</P>
<P>
   Jones, going on the advice of Aikman's two neurosurgeons,
specialists in sports-related head traumas, as well as members of
the Cowboys' medical staff, issued his no-play mandate to his
33-year-old quarterback when the latter showed up Wednesday at
Valley Ranch for business as usual.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is no doubt in my mind that this is the best thing,
short-term and long-term, for Troy _ and for the team,'' Jones
said.
</P>
<P>
   Randall Cunningham will get a chance to make his first start in
a Cowboys uniform on prime-time national television. Since his
release by Minnesota three months ago, the 37-year-old Cunningham
has had limited reps with the Cowboys until this week. He
experienced bursitis in his throwing shoulder last month.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys are 0-1 and embarrassed. Aikman is eager to ``erase
what happened'' and remains ``hopeful'' that he will play a week
from Monday night against Deion Sanders and the Washington
Redskins.
</P>
<P>
   There is no timetable, however. Aikman will be re-evaluated at
the start of each week until he returns.
</P>
<P>
   Because he incurred back-to-back concussions last season (Oct.
31 at Indianapolis and Nov. 8 at Minnesota) and missed the ensuing
two games, Aikman said, ``I think that's why there's some real
caution right now.''
</P>
<P>
   Aikman had lingering headaches (''they're pretty consistent'')
Wednesday, although he has no memory loss of those Eagles' blitzes,
and his nausea subsided Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   He has had lingering headaches with his sixth, seventh and
eighth concussions.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't take head trauma lightly,'' said Aikman, who has
studied concussions extensively the past two years] with Steve
Young and agent Leigh Steinberg, and knows that the major concern
becomes the cumulative effect of multiple concussions.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman was asked if there is any length of time away from
football that would lessen the chance of the next concussion
sidelining him ``four to six weeks, minimum,'' or is he just that
far along with eight concussions?
</P>
<P>
   ``That's a good question,'' Aikman said. ``I think if you have
concussions in consecutive weeks \Ryou don't play\S, that's what
the logic is. That's why I'm not playing this week.''
</P>
<P>
   So, why did he play against Minnesota on Nov. 8 after suffering
a concussion eight days earlier at Indianapolis?
</P>
<P>
   `` I don't know that one, either,'' Aikman said.
</P>
<P>
   His latest head injury against Philadelphia was listed as a
``mild concussion,'' to which Aikman said, ``I'm not naive enough
to think that trauma to head is `mild' in any respect.''
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, Aikman took a ``why not?'' approach to playing
this week because 1) he felt good enough, 2) a season of high
expectations still has 15 games remaining, and 3) there's no
prescribed recovery time for a concussion, anyway.
</P>
<P>
   ``There will be risk two weeks from now \Ragainst
Washington\S.''
</P>
<P>
   Aikman was honest with the situation and with himself, saying,
``I had a voice in the \Rdecision\S as well. But if it had been
left solely up to me, I would've played.''
</P>
<P>
   He doesn't know if he can help Cunningham, who gets a
personalized game plan, but he will try. Aikman will attend
meetings, but hasn't decided if he will join the team in Arizona.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
